Risk Retention Group (E) Working Group Valuation Analysis (E) Working Group View Membership Report Charges The mission of the Financial Stability (E) Task Force is to consider domestic and global financial stability issues and their impact on the role of state insurance regulators. 2026 Charges The Financial Stability (E) Task Force will: Manage the macroprudential supervisory component of the NAIC financial solvency framework. Monitor the U.S. insurance industry’s macroprudential risk levels. Maintain macroprudential regulatory tools. Identify data gaps and enhanced disclosure needs for the statutory financial statement and/or other reporting mechanisms. Propose enhancements and/or additional supervisory measures to the Financial Condition (E) Committee or other relevant committees, and consult with such committees on implementation. Monitor U.S. macroprudential policy issues, and respond as appropriate. Support and work with the state insurance regulator representative to the Financial Stability Oversight Council (FSOC) to address confidential FSOC or other federal agency macroprudential work. Participate in public FSOC or other federal agency macroprudential work. Monitor international macroprudential policy issues, and participate/respond as appropriate. Coordinate with the International Insurance Relations (G) Committee to address International Association of Insurance Supervisors (IAIS) or other international macroprudential work. Meeting Materials Exposure Drafts Documents Calendar There are no meeting materials at this time. See all Current Exposure Drafts There are no exposure drafts at this time. Related Documents Macroprudential Initiatives NAIC _ Reinsurance Comparison Worksheet 3-18-2026 Global Insurance Market Report (GIMAR) Mid-Year Update June 2025 Global Insurance Market Report (GIMAR) December 2025 Final 2024 LST Framework Final 2024 LST Framework with Lead State Guidance - For FL Final 2024 LST Framework with Lead State Guidance Final 2023 LST Fra